You are welcome to contribute to Gentoo, even when you are new to it. User contributions make Gentoo run and there is always room for improvement.

There are many different topics for you to explore; thus, that brings the question: '''Which topic is of your interest?'''

== Support the community ==

You can help users in various support mediums:

* [https://forums.gentoo.org/search.php?search_id=unanswered Answer unanswered questions], share how you solved a problem or discuss on the [https://forums.gentoo.org/ Gentoo Forums].
* [https://www.gentoo.org/main/en/irc.xml Join our IRC channels] if you prefer direct communication, the main IRC channel for users is [https://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=gentoo #gentoo].
* [https://www.gentoo.org/main/en/lists.xml Subscribe at our mailing lists], the main mailing list for users is [http://news.gmane.org/gmane.linux.gentoo.user gentoo-user].

== Document useful information ==

[https://wiki.gentoo.org Gentoo Wiki] gathers information about Gentoo and the hardware and software that it runs; you are welcome to add and edit articles:

* [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Help:Starting_a_new_page Start a new wiki article] to document a new subject, knowledge or package.
* [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Help:Editing_pages Improve existing documentation] by clicking '''Edit''' at the top right of an article.
* [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Help:Translating#For_Anyone:_Becoming_a_translator Translate documentation] for foreign readers.

== Report and resolve bugs ==

[https://bugs.gentoo.org Gentoo Bugzilla] is where we track bugs of Gentoo and its packages; you are welcome to report, confirm and resolve bugs:

* [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Beautiful_bug_reports Report a bug] at our [https://bugs.gentoo.org Gentoo Bugzilla] whenever you come across an error, flaw, failure or fault; [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Bugzilla_HOWTO Bugzilla HOWTO] provides more in-depth information when you need to provide more details.
* [https://bugs.gentoo.org/buglist.cgi?chfield=%5BBug%20creation%5D&chfieldfrom=-1D&chfieldto=Now&list_id=2122804&order=bugs.bug_id&query_format=advanced Confirm open bugs] by reproducing them, this helps consolidate the cause as well as highlight severe bugs.
* [https://sites.google.com/site/yacoset/Home/how-to-fix-bugs-step-by-step Offer solutions for open bugs]; patches, ebuilds and links to upstream (or other distribution) bug reports are welcome.
* [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Bugday Participate in our monthly Bugday], squashing bugs together with Gentoo Developers.

== Maintain and test packages ==

The Portage tree is the heart of Gentoo; it is important to keep it alive and kicking, that's why contributions to it are very valuable.

If you want to do occasional commits to either the Portage tree or an overlay, or become a Gentoo Developer; [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Basic_guide_to_write_Gentoo_Ebuilds writing ebuilds] is what makes building and installing using a package manager possible on a Gentoo system.

After the first steps, you can [https://devmanual.gentoo.org/ learn more in our Development Guide].

When you want to add a new package, update an existing one or find new packages to contribute to; these resources are for you:

* [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Bugzilla_HOWTO#Zero-day_bump_requests Report version bumps] for existing packages at our [https://bugs.gentoo.org Gentoo Bugzilla].
* [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Submitting_ebuilds Submit a new package] for the Portage tree; when you want to maintain that new package, contact the [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/qa/proxy-maintainers/index.xml proxy maintainers].
* [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/sunrise/ Join the sunrise-project], an excellent way to learn about Gentoo Development and work together with other users.
* [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/qa/proxy-maintainers/index.xml Proxy-maintain] some of our [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/qa/treecleaners/maintainer-needed.xml abandoned packages].
* [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/base/x86/arch-testers-faq.xml Become an arch tester]; for instance, check out the arch teams [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/base/x86/at.xml x86] and [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/base/amd64/at/ amd64].
* [https://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/devrel/handbook/handbook.xml Become a Gentoo Developer] and join one or more of the many herds to [https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Project:Gentoo/Staffing_Needs contribute to interesting project(s)].

